<item>
            <title>[WFLY-3537] Cookie &#8220;Expires&#8221; attribute points to a date in the past when Max-Age == 30 days</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-3537</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve documented that here:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/24351257/expires-attribute-points-to-a-date-in-the-past&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/24351257/expires-attribute-points-to-a-date-in-the-past&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and answered myself. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem came out after upgrading (from Jboss 7) to Wildfly. It&apos;s not possible to set a cookie for more than MaxInt (in miliseconds) time for IE browsers which does not support Max-Age but rely on &quot;Expires&quot; attribute, which in this case is calculated wrong. &lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;XUbuntu 14.01&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
